ProjectDesc:
When the COVID pandemic upended daily life, including the school routines of most American students and teachers, the Museum's on-line resources became an essential reference for parents, teachers, and lifelong learners. Even as other museums were forced to reduce their workforce, NWHM maintained its staff to meet this newfound demand. Like other organizations, we have been stretched to the limit financially during COVID, As such, we are requesting support for salaries and operating expenses for a period of three months to continue our work as the nation enters into a new period of COVID restrictions.<br />
<br />
NNEH support for the museum will enable it to continue to provide valuable resources to the American public during the pandemic.&nbsp;

